{
  "id": "RAW_8e2f4fdb",
  "title": "FACTS 基准套件：系统评估大型语言模型事实准确性的新方法",
  "url": "https://deepmind.google/blog/facts-benchmark-suite-systematically-evaluating-the-factuality-of-large-language-models/",
  "date": "2025-12-09 11:29:03",
  "author": "Google DeepMind Blog",
  "siteName": "Google DeepMind Blog",
  "content": "<html>\n <head></head>\n <body>\n  <main id=\"page-content\">\n   <section class=\"section-default section-cover section-cover--blog section-cover--simple\">\n    <div class=\"media-content-wrapper\">\n     <div class=\"media__container no-light-mode-mobile no-dark-mode no-dark-mode-mobile has-default-media\">\n      <div class=\"media-image-block no-light-mode-mobile no-dark-mode no-dark-mode-mobile has-default-media\">\n       <picture class=\"image --scrim media--aspect-16-9\" aria-hidden=\"false\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/UtaV3T8CfCPiTT0lP35kiMU-V9StKRTbJPJBS-aXMNeZZBHEEl7cXvx4m4plgrIn5JyG5ulISD7ycRIrRwKceUUsKcH5tXnid4WD_X6ugPDHSkaRsw=w1440-h810-n-nu\" width=\"1440\" height=\"810\" alt=\"A dark, abstract 3D visualization resembling a pie chart or a circular city map viewed from above. It is composed of many luminous vertical bars or spikes, with one large, triangular-shaped section highlighted in white and another section in glowing purple, all resting on a dark blue, studded circular base. The overall effect is futuristic and digital.\" class=\"picture__image\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1440px) 1440px, 100vw\"></picture>\n      </div>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n   </section>\n   <section class=\"grid section-default spacer-block-md-bottom section-padding-top \">\n    <div class=\"grid__inner grid__column--span-6-lg grid__column--offset-3-lg grid__column--span-8-md grid__column--offset-2-md grid__column--span-12-sm grid__column--span-12-xs\">\n     <div class=\"rich-text\">\n      <p data-block-key=\"usuz2\" class=\"lead-paragraph\">Large language models (LLMs) are increasingly becoming a primary source for information delivery across diverse use cases, so it’s important that their responses are factually accurate.</p>\n      <p data-block-key=\"fegj5\">In order to continue improving their performance on this industry-wide challenge, we have to better understand the types of use cases where models struggle to provide an accurate response and better measure factuality performance in those areas.</p>\n      <p data-block-key=\"56mrf\">Today, we’re teaming up with Kaggle to introduce the <a href=\"https://www.kaggle.com/benchmarks/google/facts/leaderboard\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">FACTS Benchmark Suite</a>. It extends our previous work developing the <a href=\"https://deepmind.google/blog/facts-grounding-a-new-benchmark-for-evaluating-the-factuality-of-large-language-models/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">FACTS Grounding Benchmark</a>, with three additional factuality benchmarks, including:</p>\n      <ul>\n       <li data-block-key=\"6qs38\">A <a href=\"https://www.kaggle.com/benchmarks/google/facts-parametric/leaderboard\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Parametric Benchmark</strong></a> that measures the model’s ability to access its internal knowledge accurately in factoid question use-cases.</li>\n       <li data-block-key=\"ebbdb\">A <a href=\"https://www.kaggle.com/benchmarks/google/facts-search/leaderboard\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Search Benchmark</strong></a> that tests a model’s ability to use Search as a tool to retrieve information and synthesize it correctly.</li>\n       <li data-block-key=\"e48rm\">A <a href=\"https://www.kaggle.com/benchmarks/google/facts-multimodal/leaderboard\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Multimodal Benchmark</strong></a> that tests a model’s ability to answer prompts related to input images in a factually correct manner.</li>\n      </ul>\n      <p data-block-key=\"enlkl\">We are also updating the original FACTS grounding benchmark with <a href=\"https://www.kaggle.com/benchmarks/google/facts-grounding/leaderboard\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Grounding Benchmark - v2</strong></a>, an extended benchmark to test a model’s ability to provide answers grounded in the context of a given prompt.</p>\n      <p data-block-key=\"1n5rs\">Each benchmark was carefully curated to produce a total of 3,513 examples, which we are making publicly available today. Similar to our previous release, we are following standard industry practice and keeping an evaluation set held-out as a private set. The FACTS Benchmark Suite Score (or FACTS Score) is calculated as the average accuracy of both public and private sets across the four benchmarks. Kaggle will oversee the management of the FACTS Benchmark Suite. This includes owning the private held-out sets, testing the leading LLMs on the benchmarks, and hosting the results on a public leaderboard. More details about the FACTS evaluation methodology can be found in our <a href=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/deepmind-media/FACTS/FACTS_benchmark_suite_paper.pdf\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">tech report</a>.</p>\n      <h2 data-block-key=\"2fes2\">Benchmark overview</h2>\n      <h3 data-block-key=\"boaug\">Parametric Benchmark</h3>\n      <p data-block-key=\"csn4k\">The FACTS Parametric benchmark assesses the ability of models to accurately answer factual questions, without the aid of external tools like web search. All the questions in the benchmark are “trivia style” questions driven by user interest that can be answered via Wikipedia (a standard source for LLM pretraining). The resulting benchmark consists of a 1052-item public set and a 1052-item private set.</p>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n   </section>\n   <section class=\"grid section-default spacer-block-md-bottom section-padding-top \">\n    <div class=\"grid__inner grid__column--span-8-md grid__column--offset-2-md grid__column--span-12-sm grid__column--span-12-xs\">\n     <div class=\"media-content-wrapper\">\n      <figure class=\"media__container has-dark-mode-alternative no-light-mode-mobile no-dark-mode-mobile\">\n       <div class=\"media-image-block has-dark-mode-alternative no-light-mode-mobile no-dark-mode-mobile\">\n        <picture class=\"image --scrim media--aspect-original  light-mode\" aria-hidden=\"false\"><source srcset=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/3rWcOoUWW4R1fPg-rubQXK7EX_LWQb-OVdjx3h5GnDHOXMIxVTWmMimghase8GzR0ih7O1fQUPLnxTkRNchdIKfZuPscCBnH-746Biyqt9a77ImKBw=w393-rw-lo 393w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/3rWcOoUWW4R1fPg-rubQXK7EX_LWQb-OVdjx3h5GnDHOXMIxVTWmMimghase8GzR0ih7O1fQUPLnxTkRNchdIKfZuPscCBnH-746Biyqt9a77ImKBw=w768-rw-lo 768w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/3rWcOoUWW4R1fPg-rubQXK7EX_LWQb-OVdjx3h5GnDHOXMIxVTWmMimghase8GzR0ih7O1fQUPLnxTkRNchdIKfZuPscCBnH-746Biyqt9a77ImKBw=w1024-rw-lo 1024w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/3rWcOoUWW4R1fPg-rubQXK7EX_LWQb-OVdjx3h5GnDHOXMIxVTWmMimghase8GzR0ih7O1fQUPLnxTkRNchdIKfZuPscCBnH-746Biyqt9a77ImKBw=w1440-rw-lo 1440w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/3rWcOoUWW4R1fPg-rubQXK7EX_LWQb-OVdjx3h5GnDHOXMIxVTWmMimghase8GzR0ih7O1fQUPLnxTkRNchdIKfZuPscCBnH-746Biyqt9a77ImKBw=w1728-rw-lo 1728w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/3rWcOoUWW4R1fPg-rubQXK7EX_LWQb-OVdjx3h5GnDHOXMIxVTWmMimghase8GzR0ih7O1fQUPLnxTkRNchdIKfZuPscCBnH-746Biyqt9a77ImKBw=w2880-rw-lo 2592w\" type=\"image/webp\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/3rWcOoUWW4R1fPg-rubQXK7EX_LWQb-OVdjx3h5GnDHOXMIxVTWmMimghase8GzR0ih7O1fQUPLnxTkRNchdIKfZuPscCBnH-746Biyqt9a77ImKBw=w1440\" width=\"1440\" height=\"882\" alt=\"Distribution of context domain (left) and distribution of the answer type (right) as a percent of the total set of questions in the Parametric benchmark.\" class=\"picture__image\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1440px) 1440px, 100vw\"></picture> <picture class=\"image --scrim media--aspect-original  dark-mode-alternative\" aria-hidden=\"false\"><source srcset=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/dfUZuvGKtW46CkqUiLvZWXBqBOGGy1lkw31AyOjVyNpuWSfO2TQxYn9w-9MEABCoHDbszZswKFTxJjoOUu8oN8IARlQs9MlLLCS3O38BahvnLB6f=w393-rw-lo 393w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/dfUZuvGKtW46CkqUiLvZWXBqBOGGy1lkw31AyOjVyNpuWSfO2TQxYn9w-9MEABCoHDbszZswKFTxJjoOUu8oN8IARlQs9MlLLCS3O38BahvnLB6f=w768-rw-lo 768w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/dfUZuvGKtW46CkqUiLvZWXBqBOGGy1lkw31AyOjVyNpuWSfO2TQxYn9w-9MEABCoHDbszZswKFTxJjoOUu8oN8IARlQs9MlLLCS3O38BahvnLB6f=w1024-rw-lo 1024w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/dfUZuvGKtW46CkqUiLvZWXBqBOGGy1lkw31AyOjVyNpuWSfO2TQxYn9w-9MEABCoHDbszZswKFTxJjoOUu8oN8IARlQs9MlLLCS3O38BahvnLB6f=w1440-rw-lo 1440w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/dfUZuvGKtW46CkqUiLvZWXBqBOGGy1lkw31AyOjVyNpuWSfO2TQxYn9w-9MEABCoHDbszZswKFTxJjoOUu8oN8IARlQs9MlLLCS3O38BahvnLB6f=w1728-rw-lo 1728w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/dfUZuvGKtW46CkqUiLvZWXBqBOGGy1lkw31AyOjVyNpuWSfO2TQxYn9w-9MEABCoHDbszZswKFTxJjoOUu8oN8IARlQs9MlLLCS3O38BahvnLB6f=w2880-rw-lo 2592w\" type=\"image/webp\"></picture>\n       </div>\n       <figcaption class=\"caption\">\n        <div class=\"caption__text text-caption caption--fill\" id=\"caption-5429c668-956d-4886-8b69-367258e8a0db\">\n         <p data-block-key=\"eta1p\">Distribution of context domain (left) and distribution of the answer type (right) as a percent of the total set of questions in the Parametric benchmark.</p>\n        </div>\n       </figcaption>\n      </figure>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n   </section>\n   <section class=\"grid section-default spacer-block-md-bottom section-padding-top \">\n    <div class=\"grid__inner grid__column--span-6-lg grid__column--offset-3-lg grid__column--span-8-md grid__column--offset-2-md grid__column--span-12-sm grid__column--span-12-xs\">\n     <div class=\"rich-text\">\n      <p data-block-key=\"usuz2\">A typical prompt from the public set would require the model to answer a simple question on a niche topic, e.g., “Who played harmonica on ‘The Rockford Files’ theme song?”</p>\n      <h3 data-block-key=\"4fpoc\">Search Benchmark</h3>\n      <p data-block-key=\"3f0j\">By contrast, the FACTS Search benchmark evaluates a model’s ability to use a web search tool for answering questions. This benchmark was designed to be challenging for LLMs even with access to the web, often requiring the retrieval of multiple facts sequentially to answer a single query. The same web search tool is being made available to all models, ensuring the model capabilities are tested in isolation without the confounding factor of custom web retrieval settings. FACTS Search consists of a 890-item public set and a 994-item private set.</p>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n   </section>\n   <section class=\"grid section-default spacer-block-md-bottom section-padding-top \">\n    <div class=\"grid__inner grid__column--span-8-md grid__column--offset-2-md grid__column--span-12-sm grid__column--span-12-xs\">\n     <div class=\"media-content-wrapper\">\n      <figure class=\"media__container has-dark-mode-alternative no-light-mode-mobile no-dark-mode-mobile\">\n       <div class=\"media-image-block has-dark-mode-alternative no-light-mode-mobile no-dark-mode-mobile\">\n        <picture class=\"image --scrim media--aspect-original  light-mode\" aria-hidden=\"false\"><source srcset=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/TjFoip4LXatWLaEeubsWJGshovmVWoxGFRAzw6HT_BYUcICF8EMvvClM8oQsn_7e34tgILFoCSN9R_OVZozgC9UQN8shMli9Uey1xpB3hUGQGtZhhA=w393-rw-lo 393w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/TjFoip4LXatWLaEeubsWJGshovmVWoxGFRAzw6HT_BYUcICF8EMvvClM8oQsn_7e34tgILFoCSN9R_OVZozgC9UQN8shMli9Uey1xpB3hUGQGtZhhA=w768-rw-lo 768w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/TjFoip4LXatWLaEeubsWJGshovmVWoxGFRAzw6HT_BYUcICF8EMvvClM8oQsn_7e34tgILFoCSN9R_OVZozgC9UQN8shMli9Uey1xpB3hUGQGtZhhA=w1024-rw-lo 1024w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/TjFoip4LXatWLaEeubsWJGshovmVWoxGFRAzw6HT_BYUcICF8EMvvClM8oQsn_7e34tgILFoCSN9R_OVZozgC9UQN8shMli9Uey1xpB3hUGQGtZhhA=w1440-rw-lo 1440w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/TjFoip4LXatWLaEeubsWJGshovmVWoxGFRAzw6HT_BYUcICF8EMvvClM8oQsn_7e34tgILFoCSN9R_OVZozgC9UQN8shMli9Uey1xpB3hUGQGtZhhA=w1728-rw-lo 1728w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/TjFoip4LXatWLaEeubsWJGshovmVWoxGFRAzw6HT_BYUcICF8EMvvClM8oQsn_7e34tgILFoCSN9R_OVZozgC9UQN8shMli9Uey1xpB3hUGQGtZhhA=w2880-rw-lo 2592w\" type=\"image/webp\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/TjFoip4LXatWLaEeubsWJGshovmVWoxGFRAzw6HT_BYUcICF8EMvvClM8oQsn_7e34tgILFoCSN9R_OVZozgC9UQN8shMli9Uey1xpB3hUGQGtZhhA=w1440\" width=\"1440\" height=\"882\" alt=\"Distribution of context domain (left) and distribution of the task requested by the user (right) as a percent of the total set of prompts in the Search benchmark.\" class=\"picture__image\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1440px) 1440px, 100vw\"></picture> <picture class=\"image --scrim media--aspect-original  dark-mode-alternative\" aria-hidden=\"false\"><source srcset=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/KLFNpI1mJYU0HcEgdo2b0kbB2F7WLxA2hCttyzfPLSzPh9gtlC7u6yBMJ-PRw0XSzgamzFuNAfnr5_2i-d1AEx7ap9VwcE5FnHghuQfVcjnbSIBAl6A=w393-rw-lo 393w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/KLFNpI1mJYU0HcEgdo2b0kbB2F7WLxA2hCttyzfPLSzPh9gtlC7u6yBMJ-PRw0XSzgamzFuNAfnr5_2i-d1AEx7ap9VwcE5FnHghuQfVcjnbSIBAl6A=w768-rw-lo 768w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/KLFNpI1mJYU0HcEgdo2b0kbB2F7WLxA2hCttyzfPLSzPh9gtlC7u6yBMJ-PRw0XSzgamzFuNAfnr5_2i-d1AEx7ap9VwcE5FnHghuQfVcjnbSIBAl6A=w1024-rw-lo 1024w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/KLFNpI1mJYU0HcEgdo2b0kbB2F7WLxA2hCttyzfPLSzPh9gtlC7u6yBMJ-PRw0XSzgamzFuNAfnr5_2i-d1AEx7ap9VwcE5FnHghuQfVcjnbSIBAl6A=w1440-rw-lo 1440w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/KLFNpI1mJYU0HcEgdo2b0kbB2F7WLxA2hCttyzfPLSzPh9gtlC7u6yBMJ-PRw0XSzgamzFuNAfnr5_2i-d1AEx7ap9VwcE5FnHghuQfVcjnbSIBAl6A=w1728-rw-lo 1728w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/KLFNpI1mJYU0HcEgdo2b0kbB2F7WLxA2hCttyzfPLSzPh9gtlC7u6yBMJ-PRw0XSzgamzFuNAfnr5_2i-d1AEx7ap9VwcE5FnHghuQfVcjnbSIBAl6A=w2880-rw-lo 2592w\" type=\"image/webp\"></picture>\n       </div>\n       <figcaption class=\"caption\">\n        <div class=\"caption__text text-caption caption--fill\" id=\"caption-8fd99292-a584-450c-a9a6-c045c760cf9a\">\n         <p data-block-key=\"eta1p\">Distribution of context domain (left) and distribution of the task requested by the user (right) as a percent of the total set of prompts in the Search benchmark.</p>\n        </div>\n       </figcaption>\n      </figure>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n   </section>\n   <section class=\"grid section-default spacer-block-md-bottom section-padding-top \">\n    <div class=\"grid__inner grid__column--span-6-lg grid__column--offset-3-lg grid__column--span-8-md grid__column--offset-2-md grid__column--span-12-sm grid__column--span-12-xs\">\n     <div class=\"rich-text\">\n      <p data-block-key=\"usuz2\">The following example from the public set was included because it requires retrieving information from several web pages, “What is the sum of the birth years of the British boxer who defeated Vazik Kazarian at the 1960 Summer Olympics, the Moroccan boxer who also competed in the men’s light welterweight event at those same Olympics, and the Danish boxer who competed in both the 1960 and 1964 Summer Olympics?”</p>\n      <h3 data-block-key=\"ucm1\">Multimodal Benchmark</h3>\n      <p data-block-key=\"7tucf\">The FACTS Multimodal benchmark evaluates the ability of models to generate factually accurate text in response to image-based questions, which is a critical capability for modern multimodal systems.</p>\n      <p data-block-key=\"794gt\">This task requires the integration of visual grounding, i.e. its ability to accurately interpret and connect information from visual input, using its internal or “parametric” world knowledge. The evaluation framework is designed to ensure that a response is both correct and provides all necessary information to be complete. The benchmark consists of a 711-item public set and a 811-item private set.</p>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n   </section>\n   <section class=\"grid section-default spacer-block-md-bottom section-padding-top \">\n    <div class=\"grid__inner grid__column--span-8-md grid__column--offset-2-md grid__column--span-12-sm grid__column--span-12-xs\">\n     <div class=\"media-content-wrapper\">\n      <figure class=\"media__container has-dark-mode-alternative no-light-mode-mobile no-dark-mode-mobile\">\n       <div class=\"media-image-block has-dark-mode-alternative no-light-mode-mobile no-dark-mode-mobile\">\n        <picture class=\"image --scrim media--aspect-original  light-mode\" aria-hidden=\"false\"><source srcset=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/o1Gr2jkpDQliiXsnwl50CttQy1VoPvIyaveYz0et8KU7zVzGp0Cv6Nmkuk92FZFTlwTym-xUnnaGGtQwKWWCqib3ryideKWR8btNhYxNr5hP2HVQ=w393-rw-lo 393w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/o1Gr2jkpDQliiXsnwl50CttQy1VoPvIyaveYz0et8KU7zVzGp0Cv6Nmkuk92FZFTlwTym-xUnnaGGtQwKWWCqib3ryideKWR8btNhYxNr5hP2HVQ=w768-rw-lo 768w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/o1Gr2jkpDQliiXsnwl50CttQy1VoPvIyaveYz0et8KU7zVzGp0Cv6Nmkuk92FZFTlwTym-xUnnaGGtQwKWWCqib3ryideKWR8btNhYxNr5hP2HVQ=w1024-rw-lo 1024w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/o1Gr2jkpDQliiXsnwl50CttQy1VoPvIyaveYz0et8KU7zVzGp0Cv6Nmkuk92FZFTlwTym-xUnnaGGtQwKWWCqib3ryideKWR8btNhYxNr5hP2HVQ=w1440-rw-lo 1440w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/o1Gr2jkpDQliiXsnwl50CttQy1VoPvIyaveYz0et8KU7zVzGp0Cv6Nmkuk92FZFTlwTym-xUnnaGGtQwKWWCqib3ryideKWR8btNhYxNr5hP2HVQ=w1728-rw-lo 1728w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/o1Gr2jkpDQliiXsnwl50CttQy1VoPvIyaveYz0et8KU7zVzGp0Cv6Nmkuk92FZFTlwTym-xUnnaGGtQwKWWCqib3ryideKWR8btNhYxNr5hP2HVQ=w2880-rw-lo 2592w\" type=\"image/webp\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/o1Gr2jkpDQliiXsnwl50CttQy1VoPvIyaveYz0et8KU7zVzGp0Cv6Nmkuk92FZFTlwTym-xUnnaGGtQwKWWCqib3ryideKWR8btNhYxNr5hP2HVQ=w1440\" width=\"1440\" height=\"882\" alt=\"Distribution of image (left) and distribution of the question categories (right) as a part of the Multimodal benchmark\" class=\"picture__image\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1440px) 1440px, 100vw\"></picture> <picture class=\"image --scrim media--aspect-original  dark-mode-alternative\" aria-hidden=\"false\"><source srcset=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/HNnmCFScFhiOAv4B7M9C6U3CHFwgZ_D2WM_TPpk96oYBLFSTQe3kM2zaqBJ-boHLu20neyvhYbO6NwImqW6rAYUyepBgGsPToEZwPjXJQhU-2EOl=w393-rw-lo 393w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/HNnmCFScFhiOAv4B7M9C6U3CHFwgZ_D2WM_TPpk96oYBLFSTQe3kM2zaqBJ-boHLu20neyvhYbO6NwImqW6rAYUyepBgGsPToEZwPjXJQhU-2EOl=w768-rw-lo 768w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/HNnmCFScFhiOAv4B7M9C6U3CHFwgZ_D2WM_TPpk96oYBLFSTQe3kM2zaqBJ-boHLu20neyvhYbO6NwImqW6rAYUyepBgGsPToEZwPjXJQhU-2EOl=w1024-rw-lo 1024w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/HNnmCFScFhiOAv4B7M9C6U3CHFwgZ_D2WM_TPpk96oYBLFSTQe3kM2zaqBJ-boHLu20neyvhYbO6NwImqW6rAYUyepBgGsPToEZwPjXJQhU-2EOl=w1440-rw-lo 1440w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/HNnmCFScFhiOAv4B7M9C6U3CHFwgZ_D2WM_TPpk96oYBLFSTQe3kM2zaqBJ-boHLu20neyvhYbO6NwImqW6rAYUyepBgGsPToEZwPjXJQhU-2EOl=w1728-rw-lo 1728w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/HNnmCFScFhiOAv4B7M9C6U3CHFwgZ_D2WM_TPpk96oYBLFSTQe3kM2zaqBJ-boHLu20neyvhYbO6NwImqW6rAYUyepBgGsPToEZwPjXJQhU-2EOl=w2880-rw-lo 2592w\" type=\"image/webp\"></picture>\n       </div>\n       <figcaption class=\"caption\">\n        <div class=\"caption__text text-caption caption--fill\" id=\"caption-77b726ab-99e6-4407-aea2-716bbe7f9207\">\n         <p data-block-key=\"eta1p\">Distribution of image (left) and distribution of the question categories (right) as a part of the Multimodal benchmark.</p>\n        </div>\n       </figcaption>\n      </figure>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n   </section>\n   <section class=\"grid section-default spacer-block-md-bottom section-padding-top \">\n    <div class=\"grid__inner grid__column--span-6-lg grid__column--offset-3-lg grid__column--span-8-md grid__column--offset-2-md grid__column--span-12-sm grid__column--span-12-xs\">\n     <div class=\"rich-text\">\n      <p data-block-key=\"usuz2\">For example, the following image from the public set of the Multimodal benchmark appeared with the prompt: “What genus does this animal belong to?”</p>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n   </section>\n   <section class=\"grid section-default spacer-block-md-bottom section-padding-top \">\n    <div class=\"grid__inner grid__column--span-6-lg grid__column--offset-3-lg grid__column--span-8-md grid__column--offset-2-md grid__column--span-12-sm grid__column--span-12-xs\">\n     <div class=\"media-content-wrapper\">\n      <figure class=\"media__container no-light-mode-mobile no-dark-mode no-dark-mode-mobile has-default-media\">\n       <div class=\"media-image-block no-light-mode-mobile no-dark-mode no-dark-mode-mobile has-default-media\">\n        <picture class=\"image --scrim media--aspect-original\" aria-hidden=\"false\"><source srcset=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/RaSYwSSlTwGVF3I3lfRKPSwC6PlsqzYRyF-SnebnRLFCuOxNOx6jY743QGT9WwM-Ze1gievuj6D60l82PulYNYjVMDct0OueMC1Oti5CmWbtCaL5Oy4=w393-rw-lo 393w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/RaSYwSSlTwGVF3I3lfRKPSwC6PlsqzYRyF-SnebnRLFCuOxNOx6jY743QGT9WwM-Ze1gievuj6D60l82PulYNYjVMDct0OueMC1Oti5CmWbtCaL5Oy4=w768-rw-lo 768w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/RaSYwSSlTwGVF3I3lfRKPSwC6PlsqzYRyF-SnebnRLFCuOxNOx6jY743QGT9WwM-Ze1gievuj6D60l82PulYNYjVMDct0OueMC1Oti5CmWbtCaL5Oy4=w1024-rw-lo 1024w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/RaSYwSSlTwGVF3I3lfRKPSwC6PlsqzYRyF-SnebnRLFCuOxNOx6jY743QGT9WwM-Ze1gievuj6D60l82PulYNYjVMDct0OueMC1Oti5CmWbtCaL5Oy4=w1440-rw-lo 1248w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/RaSYwSSlTwGVF3I3lfRKPSwC6PlsqzYRyF-SnebnRLFCuOxNOx6jY743QGT9WwM-Ze1gievuj6D60l82PulYNYjVMDct0OueMC1Oti5CmWbtCaL5Oy4=w1728-rw-lo 1248w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/RaSYwSSlTwGVF3I3lfRKPSwC6PlsqzYRyF-SnebnRLFCuOxNOx6jY743QGT9WwM-Ze1gievuj6D60l82PulYNYjVMDct0OueMC1Oti5CmWbtCaL5Oy4=w2880-rw-lo 1248w\" type=\"image/webp\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/RaSYwSSlTwGVF3I3lfRKPSwC6PlsqzYRyF-SnebnRLFCuOxNOx6jY743QGT9WwM-Ze1gievuj6D60l82PulYNYjVMDct0OueMC1Oti5CmWbtCaL5Oy4=w1440\" width=\"1248\" height=\"1186\" alt=\"Close-up photograph of a small, fuzzy brown moth or skipper butterfly with broad wings resting on a green leaf. The insect has large black eyes and antennae curved backward over its head.\" class=\"picture__image\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1440px) 1440px, 100vw\"></picture>\n       </div>\n       <figcaption class=\"caption\">\n        <div class=\"caption__text text-caption caption--fill\" id=\"caption-0516e7b2-03f9-4911-a00b-93143b00adec\">\n         <p data-block-key=\"eta1p\">An example of an image from the Multimodal benchmark (Photo credit: Image: Racta apella by desertnaturalist, CC BY 4.0)</p>\n        </div>\n       </figcaption>\n      </figure>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n   </section>\n   <section class=\"grid section-default spacer-block-md-bottom section-padding-top \">\n    <div class=\"grid__inner grid__column--span-6-lg grid__column--offset-3-lg grid__column--span-8-md grid__column--offset-2-md grid__column--span-12-sm grid__column--span-12-xs\">\n     <div class=\"rich-text\">\n      <h2 data-block-key=\"tdc97\">Results</h2>\n      <p data-block-key=\"9anhl\">We evaluated leading LLMs on the FACTS Benchmark Suite, which includes the updated FACTS Grounding v2.</p>\n      <p data-block-key=\"ar9s4\">The table below lists 15 leading models and their overall FACTS score (followed by the breakdown to the scores across the four individual benchmarks: Grounding, Multimodal, Parametric and Search).</p>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n   </section>\n   <section class=\"grid section-default spacer-block-md-bottom section-padding-top \">\n    <div class=\"grid__inner grid__column--span-8-md grid__column--offset-2-md grid__column--span-12-sm grid__column--span-12-xs\">\n     <div class=\"media-content-wrapper\">\n      <div class=\"media__container has-dark-mode-alternative no-light-mode-mobile no-dark-mode-mobile\">\n       <div class=\"media-image-block has-dark-mode-alternative no-light-mode-mobile no-dark-mode-mobile\">\n        <picture class=\"image --scrim media--aspect-original  light-mode\" aria-hidden=\"false\"><source srcset=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/abbClpiLAte-Kdj4zLeSNbsAwctgypFDfsTK33u8zqWTq_XkHzgszrv051GBbZldBg_zQ5h8gopJUw_W8P4vyRgWDBaz73j2jaVJuqj0Mscl8toe=w393-rw-lo 393w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/abbClpiLAte-Kdj4zLeSNbsAwctgypFDfsTK33u8zqWTq_XkHzgszrv051GBbZldBg_zQ5h8gopJUw_W8P4vyRgWDBaz73j2jaVJuqj0Mscl8toe=w768-rw-lo 768w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/abbClpiLAte-Kdj4zLeSNbsAwctgypFDfsTK33u8zqWTq_XkHzgszrv051GBbZldBg_zQ5h8gopJUw_W8P4vyRgWDBaz73j2jaVJuqj0Mscl8toe=w1024-rw-lo 1024w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/abbClpiLAte-Kdj4zLeSNbsAwctgypFDfsTK33u8zqWTq_XkHzgszrv051GBbZldBg_zQ5h8gopJUw_W8P4vyRgWDBaz73j2jaVJuqj0Mscl8toe=w1440-rw-lo 1440w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/abbClpiLAte-Kdj4zLeSNbsAwctgypFDfsTK33u8zqWTq_XkHzgszrv051GBbZldBg_zQ5h8gopJUw_W8P4vyRgWDBaz73j2jaVJuqj0Mscl8toe=w1728-rw-lo 1728w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/abbClpiLAte-Kdj4zLeSNbsAwctgypFDfsTK33u8zqWTq_XkHzgszrv051GBbZldBg_zQ5h8gopJUw_W8P4vyRgWDBaz73j2jaVJuqj0Mscl8toe=w2880-rw-lo 2592w\" type=\"image/webp\"></picture>\n       </div>\n      </div>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n   </section>\n   <section class=\"grid section-default spacer-block-md-bottom section-padding-top \">\n    <div class=\"grid__inner grid__column--span-6-lg grid__column--offset-3-lg grid__column--span-8-md grid__column--offset-2-md grid__column--span-12-sm grid__column--span-12-xs\">\n     <div class=\"rich-text\">\n      <p data-block-key=\"usuz2\">Gemini 3 Pro leads in overall performance, with a FACTS Score of 68.8%. In particular, we saw significant improvements from Gemini 2.5 Pro to Gemini 3 Pro in Search &amp; Parametric slices, where the error rate was reduced by 55% on FACTS Search and 35% for FACTS Parametric. FACTS Multimodal saw the lowest scores, generally. All evaluated models achieved an overall accuracy below 70%, leaving considerable headroom for future progress.</p>\n      <p data-block-key=\"3dc13\">Beyond the FACTS Benchmark Suite, Gemini’s improvement in factuality is also reflected in another factuality benchmark, <a href=\"https://www.kaggle.com/benchmarks/deepmind/simpleqa-verified\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">SimpleQA Verified</a>, going from 54.5% accuracy on Gemini 2.5 Pro to 72.1% accuracy on Gemini 3 Pro. SimpleQA Verified tests LLMs’ parametric knowledge on short-form responses.</p>\n      <h2 data-block-key=\"4jmqa\">Looking Ahead</h2>\n      <p data-block-key=\"du9pa\">While LLM factuality is still an area of ongoing research, the FACTS Benchmark Suite and Gemini 3 Pro results are representative of Google’s long-term commitment towards making information universally accessible and useful. We hope this work encourages deeper research into LLM factuality, leading to better and more accurate models and products for the people that rely on them.</p>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n   </section>\n   <section class=\"grid section-default spacer-block-md-bottom section-padding-top \">\n    <div class=\"grid__inner grid__column--span-12\">\n     <div class=\"news-group-section container spacer-block-none-bottom\">\n      <div class=\"news-group__two-column-wrapper grid\">\n       <div class=\"grid__column--span-4-xs grid__column--span-8-sm grid__column--span-6-md\">\n        <article class=\"card card-blog card--small_h\">\n         <div class=\"card__inner\">\n          <div class=\"media-content-wrapper\">\n           <div class=\"media__container\"></div>\n          </div>\n         </div>\n        </article>\n       </div>\n      </div>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n   </section>\n  </main>\n </body>\n</html>",
  "aiSummary": "Google DeepMind 推出了 FACTS 基准套件，这是一个新系统，用于评估大型语言模型（LLMs）在参数、搜索、多模态和基础任务中的事实准确性，突出了……（[请补充原始句子中省略的部分以获得完整的上下文以便重新翻译]）",
  "oneSentenceSummary": "Google DeepMind 推出了 FACTS 基准套件，这是一个新系统，用于评估大型语言模型（LLMs）在参数、搜索、多模态和基础任务中的事实准确性，突出了……（[请补充原始句子中省略的部分以获得完整的上下文以便重新翻译]）",
  "summary": "Google DeepMind 的这篇文章宣布发布 FACTS 基准套件，这是一个旨在系统评估大型语言模型（LLMs）事实准确性的新工具。该套件建立在先前的 FACTS 基础性基准（Grounding Benchmark）之上，引入了三个新基准：用于评估内部知识的参数基准（Parametric Benchmark）、用于评估外部信息检索和合成的搜索基准（Search Benchmark），以及用于图像查询中事实准确性的多模态基准（Multimodal Benchmark）。原来的基础性基准也已更新至 v2。该套件包含 3，513 个精选示例，由 Kaggle 负责管理，包括私有测试集和公共排行榜。使用该套件对领先的 LLMs 进行的初步评估显示，Gemini 3 Pro 取得了 68.8% 的最高整体 FACTS 分数，与 Gemini 2.5 Pro 相比，在搜索和参数任务中表现出显著改进。文章总结道，尽管取得了这些进展，所有评估模型的得分都低于 70%，这表明 LLMs 在事实准确性方面仍有巨大的改进空间，并鼓励在该领域进行深入研究。",
